Second Lady Karen Pence visited children receiving medical care during the Christmas season. She visited Medstar Georgetown University Hospital and Ronald McDonald House Charities of Greater Washington, DC. Mrs. Pence spoke with the children and their families, giving them coloring books and crayons. She also visited an art therapy program and showed appreciation for the art therapist's work. Mrs. Pence expressed her admiration for the children's courage and resilience and wished them better days ahead. The hospital and charity organizations were grateful for her visit, as it brought joy and excitement to the children during a difficult time.